               <history>
                  <origin><origPlace>[Italy]</origPlace>
                     <origDate notAfter="1325" notBefore="1300" calendar="Gregorian">[1300-1325]</origDate>
                  </origin>
                  <provenance> 
                     Ownership inscriptions: Samuel Treves (שמואל טריווש) 1730 (fol. 1).
                     Lieberman Marignano[?] (ליברמן מריניאנו) bought it in Asti (Italy) on 6 Shevat
                     [5]251 (26 January 1491 in the Gregorian calendar) from Heshlen/Heitlen [?]
                     (השלין/הייטלן) bat Rabbi Gershom z”l and from her son Gershom ben Moses; he
                     then sold it to Joab ben Baruch ben Neriah on 2 Iyyar [5]261 (30 April 1501 in
                     the Gregorian calendar) (fols. 4, 376v). Gershom קונציאו at Asti (Italy) in
                     [5]362 (1601-1602 in the Gregorian calendar) (fols. 4, 7r, 125r, 231r).
                     Gedaliah Isaac Treves bought it from the estate of Mordecai de’Rossi (מהאדומים)
                     in the year [5]469 (1708-1709 in the Gregorian calendar) (fol.
                     238r).
                  </provenance>

